-- Czech Stocks: AAA Auto, New World Resources Shares Are Active
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2011-12-29T16:04:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-29/czech-stocks-aaa-auto-new-world-resources-shares-are-active.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
rose 0.1 percent to 905.9 at the close in Prague, paring this
year’s losses to 26 percent.  The following were among the most active  equities (PX)  on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  AAA Auto Group NV (AAA)   advanced 1.8 percent to 17.53
koruna, the second-best performance in the PX gauge today. The
Czech chain of used-car dealerships said it bought CarWay
Assistance CZ, CarWay Group and CarWay Rent CZ to expand its
business.  New World Resources Plc (NWR)  , the biggest Czech coking-
coal producer, slipped 0.8 percent to 134.3 koruna, extending
its declines in 2011 to 50 percent. Benchmark European  coal (API2YR1) 
futures contracts dropped 0.7 percent to $113.7 a metric ton in
the Netherlands yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in  Prague  at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  